These server and client communicate with help of FIFO special file which is created with help of mkfifo syscall in linux.


Compile:

In one terminal run "gcc -o client client.c"
In second terminal run "gcc -o server server.c"

Run:

type "./client" to run client.
type "./server" to run server.


Type anything you want but make sure you type a single word, basically without any spaces.
You may use underscore in place of space.


